<section class="callout callout-warning license-check">
  <h2>License check</h2>

  {{#licenseRelevance}}
  <p>{{licenseRelevance}}</p>
  {{/licenseRelevance}}

  {{^licenseRelevance}}
  <p>
    Confirm your SAP license covers the extraction method you plan to use
    before building any pipeline. See
    <a href="/articles/runtime-vs-full-use/">Runtime vs Full Use →</a>
  </p>
  {{/licenseRelevance}}

  <div class="license-check-detail" id="license-check-detail">
    <!--
      JS-controlled variants — picker.js shows/hides the relevant block
      based on ?method= in the URL. All four variants are rendered; only
      the active one is visible at runtime.
    -->
    <div class="license-variant" data-method="odp">
      <p>
        <strong>ODP (Operational Data Provisioning)</strong> is permitted
        under both Runtime and Full Use SAP licenses when you access data
        through published CDS views via the OData API.
      </p>
      <p class="license-check-warning">
        <strong>SAP Note 3255746 (Feb 2024):</strong> Third-party tools that
        call ODP via RFC (ADF SAP CDC, Qlik, Fivetran ODP, Informatica ODP,
        etc.) are no longer permitted. Use ODP via OData, or switch to SLT.
        Verify with your licensing contact.
        <a href="https://support.sap.com/notes/3255746" target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Full note (SAP login required)</a>.
        [NEEDS_SAP_CITATION — confirm current note state]
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="license-variant" data-method="slt" hidden>
      <p>
        <strong>SLT (SAP Landscape Transformation)</strong> requires a
        <strong>Full Use SAP license</strong>. It is not permitted under
        Runtime licenses. Verify in
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f69a8fb28ac48d89de2381c2f02a1e9/license.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SLICENSE</a>
        that "SLT Landscape Transformation" is listed as Active, Type = Full
        Use before you configure anything in
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f69a8fb28ac48d89de2381c2f02a1e9/LTCO.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LTCO</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        License trap: Runtime vs Full Use
        <a href="/articles/runtime-vs-full-use/">→</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="license-variant" data-method="rfc" hidden>
      <p>
        <strong>Direct RFC</strong> extraction (e.g., RFC_READ_TABLE) is
        generally permitted for read-only access under Runtime and Full Use
        licenses, but is not recommended for production use — it bypasses
        authorization checks that released CDS views enforce and is subject
        to SAP Note 3255746 restrictions when wrapped by third-party ODP
        connectors. [NEEDS_SAP_CITATION — verify Runtime license scope for
        direct RFC read]
      </p>
      <p>
        License trap: Runtime vs Full Use
        <a href="/articles/runtime-vs-full-use/">→</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="license-variant" data-method="ref" hidden>
      <p>
        <strong>Reference mode:</strong> you are reviewing this walkthrough
        for SAP-side context only. No tool-specific pipeline steps are shown.
        Check your license before selecting a tool.
      </p>
      <p>
        License trap: Runtime vs Full Use
        <a href="/articles/runtime-vs-full-use/">→</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
// Inline snippet: switch visible license-variant on picker change.
// Runs immediately so no flash-of-wrong-content.
(function () {
  function showMethod(method) {
    var variants = document.querySelectorAll('.license-variant');
    variants.forEach(function (el) {
      if (el.getAttribute('data-method') === method) {
        el.removeAttribute('hidden');
      } else {
        el.setAttribute('hidden', '');
      }
    });
  }

  function readMethod() {
    var params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    return params.get('method') || 'odp';
  }

  // Apply on load.
  showMethod(readMethod());

  // Re-apply when picker radios change (picker.js fires change events).
  document.addEventListener('change', function (e) {
    if (e.target && e.target.name === 'method') {
      showMethod(e.target.value);
    }
  });
})();
</script>
